print("### Tomato and Cheese Sandwich Recipe\n\n#### Ingredients:\n- 1 packet of tomatoes\n- 1 packet of cheese\n- 1 packet of bread\n\n#### Instructions:\n\n1. **Prepare Ingredients:**\n   - Wash the tomatoes thoroughly under running water.\n   - Slice the tomatoes into thin, even slices.\n   - Open the cheese packet and separate slices (or grate if using a block).\n\n2. **Assemble the Sandwich:**\n   - Take out 2 slices of bread from the packet.\n   - Lay one slice of bread flat on a clean surface or plate.\n   - Place a layer of tomato slices on top of the bread slice.\n   - Add cheese slices (or sprinkle grated cheese) on top of the tomatoes.\n   \n3. **Complete the Sandwich:**\n   - Place the second slice of bread on top of the cheese.\n\n4. **Toast the Sandwich (Optional):**\n   - Heat a non-stick pan on medium heat.\n   - Place the sandwich onto the pan and toast until the bread turns golden brown and the cheese melts, about 2-3 minutes per side. \n\n5. **Serve:**\n   - Remove the sandwich from the pan.\n   - Let it cool slightly and serve.\n   - Optionally, you can cut the sandwich in half for easier handling.\n\nEnjoy your tomato and cheese sandwich!")